Backend Engineer
Remote

 Who we are

Everli is Europe’s leading marketplace for online grocery shopping and one of its fastest growing scale-ups. Supported by international world-class investors, we are on a mission to deliver customers peace of mind with a trouble-free grocery experience they love and trust.

We achieve our growth through a culture that is collaborative, transparent, data-driven and focused on our mission.
Our rapidly growing and diverse international team (20 nationalities and counting) has offices located in Italy (with headquarters in Milan & Verona), France and Poland and we have many remote job opportunities in other countries as well.

Hey, you!
Every month we have millions of sessions and hundreds of thousands of users on the platform. Our apps have more than a million downloads. Customers create thousands of orders every day in multiple countries.
But we want more and we need your help to achieve it.

Things like category and product listing, offers, cart handling, checkout, payments and authentication are part of the daily agenda. But that's not all! We have our own advanced search engine and fraud detection mechanisms, a detailed order tracker for our customers, a subscription system, push notifications and much more. Everything is done through REST APIs, consumed by our website and apps, while always keeping an eye on security and the privacy of our users.

If you care about customers and their needs, if you are not afraid of pushing code used by millions and you are always up-to-date with new technologies, then we are looking for you to join our Tech team!

What you will do:
You will join a small distributed team of developers with decision-making autonomy: you will be responsible for your work;
You will be part of an autonomous and heterogeneous squad, working closely with other areas, like Product, Design and Analytics;
You will find brilliant solutions for complex problems and own the process from the analysis to the delivery;
You will ship high-quality software: well-designed, well-tested and scalable.

Requirements:
Love for coding: you are proud of your work;
Knowledge of technologies in our stack: PHP (Laravel), Redis, RabbitMQ, MySQL, ElasticSearch;
Experience with REST APIs and Single Page Applications;
Experience in designing, building and shipping infrastructure for traffic-intensive applications;
Great communication and synthesis skills;
Analytical, detail-focused mindset, but always looking at the big picture;
Team player: you work well with other people within and outside the tech team;
Positive & chill vibes. Meme skills is a nice to have

Being able to legally work in Europe: you are the holder of an EU Passport or you are the holder of an EU residency permit or you are the holder of a Schengen Work Visa.

Why you should join us now:
You have the chance to change the life of millions of people;
You can rely on talented and collaborative colleagues who will both push and support you;
You receive a budget to create your own home workstation;
You can choose your preferred work laptop (Mac/PC) and use a software license budget;
You get a yearly training budget for online courses, books, conferences or workshops;
You have flexible working conditions (our team is fully remote since 2017);
You have a discount on your grocery with Everli.com;
Everli is proud to be an equal opportunity employer. We foster an inclusive and diverse workplace. No matter who you are, what you look like or how many years ago you have started your career: you will always be welcome in our team. Just like in a grocery store, diversity is richness!

Synaltic DATA ENGINEER KAFKA M/F
Synaltic is, since 2004, an ESN specialist in data management with a particular appetite for Open Source technologies.
Above all, we are known for finding solutions! Synaltic was among the first to sign Talend and Tableau customers in France. Synaltic has largely participated in the creation of the Hadoop User Group France and in the promotion of Kubernetes. Synaltic recently announced new partnerships: PowerSlide and Dremio.
The Synaltic team is made up of about thirty people, the average age is 30 years old. The head office is in Vincennes, our consultants work from our premises, customer premises and sometimes telework.
The SynalTeam seeks to strengthen itself. We are looking for a KAFKA Data Engineer specialized in CDI in Vincennes (94).
Required profile :
You have a higher education or have developed equivalent skills during your various experiences;
You have at least one significant experience with Kafka (development with the solution or configuration and integration);
You have a good understanding of business intelligence and its challenges;
Experience as a consultant would be a plus;
You are curious, jack of all trades and have a spirit of initiative;
You know how to collaborate in a team and be autonomous in your tasks;
You have a keen sense of analysis and know how to render it both orally and in writing;
The position is aimed at curious and jack-of-all-trades profiles: your openness to other technologies (ETL Talend, streaming, java, Scala, Spark, etc.) would be a plus. Our goal is to support all our consultants towards a global knowledge of data engineering.
Experience related to these subjects of more than two years is expected.
Within the Synalteam, your missions will be the following:
Understand and advise a technical architecture on the known bricks;
Interpret a need and respond to a technical problem for a client;
Carry out, document and transmit technical operations;
Technology watch, knowledge sharing internally and with our community;
Develop skills and learn new technologies.
Your role within the projects and the team will be determined and adapted according to your experience and your desire for development (Developer, Lead Tech, Solution Architect).
