SFR Within SFR's Data Department (SFR Analytics), the "Advertising & Audience Services" division processes, uses and monetizes massive SFR data on 2 markets: TV audience and digital/TV advertising.
Within this division, you will join the team that uses TV audience data from SFR boxes and applications to develop data offers for the main players in the TV and advertising market (TV channels, producers , advertising agencies, agencies).
As a Data Engineer, you will be responsible for the monitoring and evolution of our platforms and modules related to audience data, in particular our real-time TV audience measurement service.
In this high-growth environment, you will benefit from significant autonomy and you will know how to be proactive in developing, maintaining and upgrading our Big Data solutions.
In this context, your missions will be to:
1- Develop Audiences data offers, and manage the quality of data flows:
Develop and maintain data streams (kafka, rabbitMQ...) from different internal data sources (live TV data, Replay, streaming platforms...);
Use the data collected in the Data Lake to produce TV audiences, process them, make them available to our external partners;
Drive continuous optimization of resources (storage volume and computing capacity/speed);
Develop, deploy and maintain a complex architecture in production: specifications, design, monitoring, alerting, incident management etc...
2- Migrate the architecture of our Big Data platform to a new environment (Cloud).
On this occasion, you may be required to totally or partially rewrite the existing code.
3- Propose and build innovative solutions, to make them new sources of growth
Reuse of the existing for new partners.
Deployment of new solutions around Audience/Advertising data
