Voysen About Voysen
Voysen's mission is to help companies understand consumers by centralizing and analyzing the opinions left on online sales platforms. Analyzing these reviews using advanced Deep Learning (AI) and Natural Language Processing (NLP) technologies makes it possible to precisely determine what consumers like or dislike about a product and therefore obtain qualified insights. on the perception of products, brands and market trends.
Voysen therefore builds technological solutions for cosmetics and agri-food companies so that they can have quick and easy access to all types of information on their products, competitors' products and the markets in which they operate.
- Creation date: 2020
- Location: Station F, Paris
- Number of people in the company: 7
Job Description
Voysen helps businesses understand their consumers by processing and analyzing reviews available on online retail platforms like Amazon, Walmart, Sephora, etc. Today, the solutions put in place by Voysen help companies by processing several million reviews of + 60,000 products and + 5,000 brands all over the planet in several languages ​​such as: French, English, Spanish and Chinese.
On the Data Engineer position, you will join the Voysen Data team and you will work on:
The development of new NLP and Deep Learning models to extract new information contained in a consumer opinion (ex: emotion detection, keyword extraction, bot detector, etc.) using the latest research innovations scientific on the subject;
Improving the NLP models currently in production;
Model deployment and management;
Creation and management of data architectures;
Creation and management of data pipelines;
Your work at Voysen will therefore be at the crossroads of a Data Engineer, Machine Learning Engineer and Data Architect position. You will therefore participate in the generation of the data used by our customers each month.
The technical stacks used are:
Language: Python, SQL;
Machine Learning frameworks: Tensorflow, Transformers, Scikit-learn;
Pipeline frameworks: Airflow, Papermill;
Architecture: Data Lake, AWS;
Database: PostgreSQL;
DevOps: AWS, Heroku, Docker, Kubernetes.
Benefits
Participation in the development of technological solutions;
The models you develop will be deployed and used by our customers;
The architectures you develop will be directly used to process data;
The opportunity to have responsibilities;
The entrepreneurial environment at Station F;
Technical training on new languages ​​and frameworks.
Missions
Design and develop NLP models;
Manage the release of NLP models;
Design and develop data architectures;
Optimize architectures in production;
Design and develop data processing pipelines;
Integrate development and deployment cycles.
Required profile
You are looking for a complete and very versatile position in the fields of data and AI.
You are comfortable with Python and object-oriented programming (OOP) to develop applicable and scalable solutions.
You have already developed Deep Learning and/or NLP models using Deep Learning libraries (Tensorflow, Pytorch, Transformers, etc.).
You are familiar with data architectures and pipelines for automatically processing data at scale.
You are demanding in the cleanliness and durability of your code. You are used to documenting and presenting your code.
You develop your solutions with scalability and robustness in mind when data volumes will be greater than today.
