Disneyland Paris Job summary:
Here is your chance to live a unique professional adventure!

Your environment?

Disneyland Paris is currently undergoing a data transformation by acquiring a centralized team (Data Office) and a data platform on AWS to exploit its rich and varied data: digital, ticketing, accommodation, operations, maintenance, finance, shops, restaurants , supply chain, costumes, flows, human resources…

The Disneyland Paris Data Office is at the heart of this transformation and pilot project:
The maintenance and evolution of our data platform, the centralization of data within a data lake, the production of value from our data;
Promoting the use of data and accelerating self-BI to reduce analysis and decision-making times;
Animation of user communities;
The definition and development of data-driven products based on artificial intelligence.

We put data at the heart of strategic decisions and facilitate access to data for everyone. We encourage our teams to realize the potential of data, to realize its power and help them innovate.

In this context, we are recruiting a Data Engineer who will intervene in the deployment of data use cases at the service of the businesses, by the methods of data collection until its exposure and by contributing to the implementation of machine learning pipeline.

You will join the Data team made up of around thirty people and will report to the Senior Manager Decisions. You will contribute to the progress of our squads, in collaboration with the other members of the data team (Product Owner, Data Engineer, BI Developer, Data Steward, Tester), in a stimulating environment, where team spirit and the will continuous improvement & learning are key!

Each member of the team has the opportunity to be an actor in what we put in place. You will thus have the opportunity to bring your knowledge, to question the existing, to innovate, to set up new things constantly and quickly!

Your assignments?

You will actively participate in the construction of our data platform and the choice of tools, will help in decision-making and in developing the growth of Disneyland Paris.

Your missions consist, in particular, of:
Study and implement the best technical solutions to manage large volumes of data, from training data collection to production deployment;
Control the quality of the code put into production to ensure the run (Git, model performance evaluation);
Work in collaboration with the Data Engineer, Data Scientist and Product Owner to integrate machine learning models as deliverables in a product;
Develop and maintain our stack data at the state of the art;
Contribute through new data pipelines:
Collect on our datalake (S3), develop and maintain DP input and output streams, on internal and external data, in batch and realtime, until data activation (Snowflake / Redshift / Tableau, Apis…)
Transform the collected data, enrich and maintain our data warehouse (Snowflake)
Ensure the integrity of the data lifecycle
Design, set up and maintain the entire production pipeline to deploy machine learning models with Data Scientists
Propose, implement and support best practices within the data organization (agile, code review, etc.);
Practice technology watch on the cloud and data engineering.
You will have the opportunity to work on various technologies. Our current technical environment, under construction and therefore not exhaustive, is based on AWS Glue / S3 / EC2 / Sagemaker, Snowflake, Python, Spark, SQL, Git.

Joining us is the guarantee of participating in the birth of the data platform project and having an impact in its structuring and technological choices! You will have the opportunity to work on a wide variety of subjects, with the support of the Data Science & Engineering teams of The Walt Disney Company in the United States.



Your strengths for success?

You are the ideal candidate for this position if:
You have a higher education such as an engineering school or a master's degree specializing in data engineering/big data/cloud engineering/data science and have acquired a minimum of 5 years' experience in data projects, within a international and agile environment;
You know at least one cloud environment (AWS or GCP) and have already deployed code on it;
You have already participated in a datawarehouse project;
You master a programming language (Python and SQL in priority) or YAML configuration, know DevOps concepts (Docker, Kubernetes) and managed services (AWS);
You have experience in the industrialization of machine learning models ( Data Engineer F/H - CDI Montévrain (77) Interview with our data engineer to give you a broader view of the position and assess your technical abilities.

